    "is_generated": false,
    "segments": [
      {
        "start": 0.2,
        "duration": 1.2,
        "text": "- [David] Wordsmiths, hello."
      },
      {
        "start": 1.4,
        "duration": 2.4,
        "text": "I'm on an archeological dig with my pal,"
      },
      {
        "start": 3.8,
        "duration": 2.4,
        "text": "Harrison Stockbury Smythe-Smythe."
      },
      {
        "start": 6.2,
        "duration": 0.8,
        "text": "How are you, Harry?"
      },
      {
        "start": 7.1,
        "duration": 2.0,
        "text": "- [Harry] I'm spiffing, David, old thing."
      },
      {
        "start": 9.1,
        "duration": 3.1,
        "text": "One never knows what marvels\none might find at a dig site,"
      },
      {
        "start": 12.1,
        "duration": 0.8,
        "text": "does one?"
      },
      {
        "start": 13.0,
        "duration": 0.8,
        "text": "- [David] There's one."
      },
      {
        "start": 13.8,
        "duration": 0.8,
        "text": "- [Harry] What?"
      },
      {
        "start": 14.6,
        "duration": 0.8,
        "text": "- [David] Poking out of the ground."
      },
      {
        "start": 15.5,
        "duration": 1.4,
        "text": "Look, use your little brush thingy."
      },
      {
        "start": 16.8,
        "duration": 1.0,
        "text": "- [Harry] My word."
      },
      {
        "start": 17.8,
        "duration": 1.7,
        "text": "- [David] Well, our words, right?"
      },
      {
        "start": 19.5,
        "duration": 1.4,
        "text": "They belong to everyone."
      },
      {
        "start": 20.9,
        "duration": 2.8,
        "text": "- [Harry] Current, thus, despite."
      },
      {
        "start": 23.6,
        "duration": 1.7,
        "text": "What a curious collection."
      },
      {
        "start": 25.4,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "- [David] I can take over\nfrom here if you want, Harry."
      },
      {
        "start": 27.5,
        "duration": 0.8,
        "text": "- [Harry] Smashing."
      },
      {
        "start": 28.4,
        "duration": 1.4,
        "text": "Carry on, my good man."
      },
      {
        "start": 29.7,
        "duration": 1.4,
        "text": "I'll keep digging here."
      },
      {
        "start": 31.1,
        "duration": 1.6,
        "text": "Let a fellow know if you need him."
      },
      {
        "start": 32.7,
        "duration": 1.1,
        "text": "- [David] Will do."
      },
      {
        "start": 33.8,
        "duration": 0.8,
        "text": "All right, wordsmiths."
      },
      {
        "start": 34.7,
        "duration": 0.9,
        "text": "Let's get to it."
      },
      {
        "start": 35.6,
        "duration": 4.3,
        "text": "Current, thus, despite: meanings,\norigins, use in sentences."
      },
      {
        "start": 39.9,
        "duration": 0.8,
        "text": "Let's go."
      },
      {
        "start": 41.8,
        "duration": 3.5,
        "text": "So, current is both an\nadjective and a noun."
      },
      {
        "start": 45.2,
        "duration": 1.5,
        "text": "I'll do the adjective first."
      },
      {
        "start": 46.7,
        "duration": 3.8,
        "text": "It means up to date,\nrelating to the present time."
      },
      {
        "start": 50.4,
        "duration": 3.8,
        "text": "As an adverb, currently, it\nmeans in an up-to-date way."
      },
      {
        "start": 54.2,
        "duration": 4.3,
        "text": "But as a noun, it means the\nflow of a river or an ocean,"
      },
      {
        "start": 58.5,
        "duration": 1.5,
        "text": "or the flow of electricity."
      },
      {
        "start": 60.0,
        "duration": 4.7,
        "text": "Thus is an adverb which means\nas a result, for that reason."
      },
      {
        "start": 64.7,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "And despite is a preposition."
      },
      {
        "start": 66.9,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "We haven't talked about\none of those in a minute."
      },
      {
        "start": 69.1,
        "duration": 2.9,
        "text": "It means even though or in spite of."
      },
      {
        "start": 72.0,
        "duration": 4.0,
        "text": "Now, let's dust off these\nfinds in the word origin zone."
      },
      {
        "start": 76.0,
        "duration": 1.5,
        "text": "Follow me."
